This is the slack webhook for slash commands .It takes an example of displaying github user info on slash commands.
I am using python library chalice (microservice farmework) supported by aws to deploy my application on aws lambda with aws api gateway as my triggereing enpoint to lambda.
For more details check the links in reference section.
Deployment Command is 
chalice deploy --stage <name>
update  config.json in .chalice directory to set environment variables
Reference URLS
	https://renzo.lucioni.xyz/serverless-slash-commands-with-python/
	https://hackernoon.com/creating-a-serverless-python-api-using-aws-lambda-chalice-d321dc43ce2
	https://github.com/aws/chalice
	https://github.com/beregond/jsonmodels